Tcl (Tool Command Language) 
Tcl is an interpreted scripting language used in NS-2 to: 
● Create nodes and links 
● Schedule events 
● Control simulations 
Every NS-2 simulation starts with a Tcl script.

Procedure: 
1. Open Terminal. 
2. Install tcl 
>sudo apt install tcl 
3. Create Tcl file: 
> nano hello.tcl 
3. Type the program and save the file 
# Hello World program in Tcl 
puts "Hello World" 
4. Execute the program: 
> tclsh hello.tcl 
Expected Output: 
Hello World 

